  - key: ''
    value: The 'ox dream' (소 꿈) is a traditional auspicious omen in East Asian culture, often signifying the birth of a virtuous and capable person who will bring glory to the family.
  - key: ''
    value: The examination of the National Academy (성균시) and the higher civil service examination (대과) were the two principal paths to advancement in Joseon bureaucracy.
  - key: ''
    value: The 'Internal Rebellion' (내난) refers to a succession crisis in 1468 when Prince Sanwon, who had been regent, was deposed by his younger brother, the future Seongjong. Park Gong's role in assisting the reigning king during this turbulent period significantly elevated his prestige.
  - key: ''
    value: The term '기이' (strange and wondrous) reflects both the literal miraculous nature of the omen and Park Gong's exceptional qualities as a leader and administrator.
  - key: ''
    value: Sejo, the reign title here, refers to the period of King Sejo (r. 1455-1468), who was known for his military reforms and attention to astronomical and scientific advancement.
